<dl>
<dt>Books based on personal experiences</dt>
</dl>
<p>While the substance of many of Orwell's novels, particularly <i>Burmese Days</i>, is drawn from his personal experiences, the following are works presented as narrative documentaries, rather than being fictional.</p>
<ul>
<li>1933&#160;– <i><a href="Down_and_Out_in_Paris_and_London" title="Down and Out in Paris and London">Down and Out in Paris and London</a></i></li>
<li>1937&#160;– <i><a href="The_Road_to_Wigan_Pier" title="The Road to Wigan Pier">The Road to Wigan Pier</a></i></li>
<li>1938&#160;– <i><a href="Homage_to_Catalonia" title="Homage to Catalonia">Homage to Catalonia</a></i></li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=George_Orwell&action=edit&section=28.php.html" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
